physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Fetus weighed 250g, head circumference of 17.5 cm, abdominal circumference of 1.5 cm, interpupillary distance of 2.5 cm, inner canthal distance of 1.5 cm. Features: high forehead, hypertelorism, crease below lower eyelids, depressed broad nasal bridge, anteverted nares, broad nasal base, long thin philtrum, low-set ears, small mouth, microretrognathia. Short neck, bilateral hitchhiker thumb, bilateral single transverse crease, bilateral club foot (right side more severe), left fifth toe curved and dorsiflexed, right foot with increased gap between T1/T2 and T4/T5, right T5 slightly deviated. Observed bowing of lower limbs.
Increased nuchal translucency (3.1 mm) and increased nuchal fold thickness (5.3 mm).
Ultrasound showed bilateral short femur length (1.55 cm), tibia (1.28 cm), humerus (1.39 cm), radius (1.56 cm), ulna (1.59 cm), all greater than 4 SD below the mean.
